        Creates an Assignments object that generates AssignmentIterators. These can be used to efficiently iterate over all possible assignments for variables in a given rule.
        Parameters:
        headAssignment - An assignment of variables whose values should be fixed. May be empty.
        rule - The rule whose assignments we want to iterate over.
        varDomains - A map containing the possible values for each variable in the rule. (All such values are GdlConstants.)

      • getBestIterationOrderCandidate

        protected static AssignmentsImpl.IterationOrderCandidate getBestIterationOrderCandidate(GdlRule rule,
                                                                     java.util.Map<GdlVariable,java.util.Set<GdlConstant>> varDomains,
                                                                     java.util.Map<SentenceForm,AssignmentsImpl.ConstantForm> constantForms,
                                                                     java.util.Map<SentenceForm,java.lang.Integer> completedSentenceFormSizes,
                                                                     java.util.Map<GdlVariable,GdlConstant> preassignment,
                                                                     boolean analyticFunctionOrdering,
                                                                     SentenceFormSource sentenceFormSource)
        Finds the iteration order (including variables, functions, and source conjuncts) that is expected to result in the fastest iteration. The value that is compared for each ordering is the product of: - For each source conjunct, the number of tuples offered by the conjunct; - For each variable not defined by a function, the size of its domain.
        Parameters:
        constantForms -
        completedSentenceFormSizes - For each sentence form, this may optionally contain the number of possible sentences of this form. This is useful if the number of sentences is much lower than the product of its variables' domain sizes; however, if this contains sentence forms where the set of sentences is unknown, then it may return an ordering that is unusable.
